1
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,001
KIRA'S IDENTITY

2
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:26,044
[MC] So you're saying
one of those people is Kira, right?

3
00:01:26,128 --> 00:01:27,129
[Matsuda, voice disguised]
Yes.

4
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:28,735
I've got a lot of evidence
to prove it, too.

5
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:30,882
The man who died was Mr. H.

6
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:33,885
[L] If Higuchi can kill
by looking at someone's face

7
00:01:33,969 --> 00:01:36,054
like the second Kira was able to,

8
00:01:36,305 --> 00:01:38,557
-Matsuda will die.
-[Matsuda gasps]

9
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,392
SPECIAL REPORT ON KIRA
THE CONCLUSION

10
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,394
TODAY'S SHOW WILL REVEAL
THE TRUE IDENTITY OF KIRA

11
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:44,479
It's... It's him!

12
00:01:44,688 --> 00:01:47,316
[screaming] Don't screw with me.
Why the hell can't you remember

13
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:49,276
the names of the people you hire.

14
00:01:49,693 --> 00:01:51,695
That means I have two hours.

15
00:01:55,616 --> 00:01:57,117
[engine revs]

16
00:01:58,827 --> 00:02:00,203
[tires squeal]

17
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:05,959
[Wedy]
I see Higuchi.

18
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:08,420
He's only carrying a single bag.
I'm in pursuit.

19
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:11,256
[Kyosuke Higuchi] I'll kill him.
I'll kill him no matter what.

20
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:14,343
I'm not giving up until I have everything.

21
00:02:14,635 --> 00:02:17,554
FRENZY

22
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:19,139
[voice-over] Cosme Misa.

23
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:22,267
A devilish charm.
An angel's glitter.

24
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:25,646
Misa's new line of lipstick
just for you.

25
00:02:27,898 --> 00:02:30,108
Ryuzaki, the commercial's almost over.

26
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:31,443
Oh, is that so?

27
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,779
[Matsuda] Next thing you know,
I'm in a hotel room,

28
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:35,739
drinking with all eight of them.

29
00:02:35,906 --> 00:02:37,866
[MC laughs]
Well, that's rather amusing.

30
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,701
[Matsuda] But if I give you
any more details,

31
00:02:39,785 --> 00:02:41,578
I'm afraid the people who were there
that night

32
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:43,664
would realize
which one of them is Kira.

33
00:02:43,789 --> 00:02:45,957
So I think I'd better leave it at that
for now.

34
00:02:46,083 --> 00:02:48,043
[MC] Of course.
Please take your time to tell us

35
00:02:48,126 --> 00:02:50,462
all the details of your ordeal
to find Kira.

36
00:02:50,754 --> 00:02:53,965
[L] Light, please put Higuchi's car
on audio channel one.

37
00:02:54,091 --> 00:02:55,717
and Sakura TV on channel two.

38
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:58,387
[Light Yagami] As expected,
Higuchi is watching every minute of this

39
00:02:58,470 --> 00:02:59,471
from his car.

40
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:02,516
[MC] And so, according to you,
it was actually at that party

41
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:03,850
that you met Kira.

42
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,560
[Matsuda] Yes.
But of course at the time,

43
00:03:05,686 --> 00:03:08,271
I had no way of knowing
he was actually Kira.

44
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:11,400
[MC] So, that means he saw your face.
This is incredible.

45
00:03:11,483 --> 00:03:13,026
I think it's amazingly courageous of you

46
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:14,861
to step forward and appear
on this program.

47
00:03:14,945 --> 00:03:16,863
-Are you sure you're okay with it?
-[Matsuda] Yes.

48
00:03:16,947 --> 00:03:18,699
After I started investigating him,

49
00:03:18,782 --> 00:03:20,951
I found out there are two things
Kira has to have

50
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:22,160
in order to kill someone.

51
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:26,289
There are rumors on TV and the internet
as to what those two things might be

52
00:03:26,498 --> 00:03:27,791
but I know the truth.

53
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,544
[Higuchi]
A name and a face.

54
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:33,130
[Matsuda] But Kira only knows
one of those two things about me.

55
00:03:33,255 --> 00:03:34,715
so that means I should be safe.

56
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:37,342
[Higuchi] So he's saying he feels
safe enough to step forward

57
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:39,386
just because I don't know
his real name.

58
00:03:40,095 --> 00:03:41,638
Wait a minute, does that mean

59
00:03:41,805 --> 00:03:43,849
there's nothing left that can connect me
to his name?

60
00:03:44,099 --> 00:03:46,518
Maybe he's already destroyed his file
at Yoshida.

61
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:48,395
Am I'm wasting my time?

62
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:51,857
Rem, what do you think?

63
00:03:52,315 --> 00:03:54,609
What do I think? About what, may I ask?

64
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:56,611
Rem, who's that?

65
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:59,114
There's no one else in that car, right?

66
00:03:59,279 --> 00:04:02,654
It's impossible for someone to be hiding
without us knowing.

67
00:04:02,768 --> 00:04:04,686
He isn't using his cell phone.

68
00:04:05,162 --> 00:04:06,538
Could it be a hidden radio?

69
00:04:06,705 --> 00:04:09,708
No. There's aren't any radios
or other devices.

70
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:13,754
Only the bugs, cameras, and tracking
beacons that Wedy placed.

71
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:16,006
I have no doubt that she did
a thorough job.

72
00:04:16,381 --> 00:04:18,341
Do you think I'll get
to Yoshida Productions

73
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:20,469
only to find his file isn't there?

74
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,387
Is he talking to himself?

75
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:26,975
Why ask my opinion? I don't see how
I'm supposed to know something like that.

76
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:28,602
If this guy was smart,

77
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:31,146
he would destroy everything
that connects him with his real name

78
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:32,355
before he appeared on TV.

79
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:34,900
[Higuchi] And don't you think
it's a little too reckless

80
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:38,111
for Yoshida Productions to just let me
into their offices unsupervised?

81
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:40,572
Hm, maybe not. If there was a robbery

82
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:43,784
they'd figure out right away who did it,
since I know where the key is.

83
00:04:44,201 --> 00:04:45,827
This isn't sounding very good.

84
00:04:46,203 --> 00:04:48,580
He'll still go there,
don't you worry.

85
00:04:48,872 --> 00:04:51,374
Even if he does have a file at Yoshida,

86
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:53,502
it could be just another alias.

87
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:57,714
Damn it. I wouldn't put it past this guy
to do something like that.

88
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:58,882
No wonder he's confident.

89
00:04:59,716 --> 00:05:01,551
[Rem] It must be Light and Misa's plan

90
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:04,304
to have Higuchi go
to Yoshida Productions.

91
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:06,097
If that's the case...

92
00:05:06,515 --> 00:05:09,518
That may be true,
but if he knows that you are Kira,

93
00:05:09,601 --> 00:05:11,853
he's going to announce your name
in public.

94
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:13,939
That's an inescapable fact.

95
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:16,066
[MC]
All right, there's only one hour left

96
00:05:16,191 --> 00:05:17,359
until the big announcement.

97
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:19,653
Your only option is to go.

98
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:23,365
If the name on his file is false
that will be unfortunate.

99
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:25,951
But if it isn't,
you can kill him discretely

100
00:05:26,076 --> 00:05:27,369
with the notebook.

101
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,913
Yeah, I already know that much
myself.

102
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:31,540
But just to be on the safe side,

103
00:05:31,623 --> 00:05:34,543
I should kill the people
I contacted at Yoshida Productions.

104
00:05:34,626 --> 00:05:37,462
That includes the president, Misa,
and that manager of hers.

105
00:05:37,838 --> 00:05:39,881
What? No way, he's going to kill me?

106
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:41,591
It's all right. Don't worry.

107
00:05:41,675 --> 00:05:44,219
He's talking about doing that
after he's killed Matsuda.

108
00:05:44,386 --> 00:05:46,555
There would be no point in killing
the rest of you

109
00:05:46,638 --> 00:05:48,348
until he's gotten rid of
the main threat.

110
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,891
That's true, but still...

111
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,436
[Rem] Don't be reckless.
He's the only one you have to kill.

112
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:56,857
If the people you called
end up dying too,

113
00:05:56,982 --> 00:05:59,693
the phone records will implicate you
in their deaths.

114
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:03,530
Oh yeah. Rem, I didn't think
you were so smart.

115
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:07,158
Then I'll make them all erase
their call histories before they die.

116
00:06:07,534 --> 00:06:11,162
But the telephone company
will still have a record of the calls.

117
00:06:11,329 --> 00:06:13,456
There's no way he can
just be talking to himself.

118
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:16,376
But, who's Rem? Who is he talking to?

119
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:20,046
If he's talking to someone right now,
it could be...

120
00:06:21,131 --> 00:06:22,465
a Shinigami.

121
00:06:22,591 --> 00:06:23,675
[Misa whimpers]

122
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:26,136
Perhaps.

123
00:06:27,554 --> 00:06:29,931
[Rem] I should just go ahead and ask him.

124
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:33,852
How about giving up ownership
of the notebook and returning it to me?

125
00:06:33,977 --> 00:06:36,396
No, I'd end up being ruined
if I did that.

126
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:38,023
Even if I forgot the notebook

127
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:40,609
this guy says he has concrete evidence
to back him up.

128
00:06:40,692 --> 00:06:43,445
If he points out Yotsuba's recent growth
on the air

129
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:46,698
no one would ever doubt his claims.
They'd believe whatever he said.

130
00:06:46,865 --> 00:06:51,042
That means whoever he says is Kira
will be marked as Kira.

131
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:54,205
Even if he didn't have proof
and I got rid of the evidence

132
00:06:54,289 --> 00:06:56,458
by returning the notebook,
my life would be over.

133
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,794
I wouldn't get promoted, I wouldn't even
be able to stay with Yotsuba.

134
00:07:00,378 --> 00:07:02,839
[MC] Of course, Sakura TV has
broadcast this show

135
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:04,925
under the premise that right now,
as we speak,

136
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:06,468
Kira is watching this program.

137
00:07:06,968 --> 00:07:09,429
[Matsuda] In that case,
I'll take this chance to call out to him.

138
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:12,265
Kira, please turn yourself in.

139
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:15,268
[Higuchi] The guy is acting like
a complete idiot.

140
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:19,105
Still, he was smart enough to fake his own
death to avoid being killed.

141
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:22,776
-I have to kill him as soon as possible.
-[tires squeal]

142
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:25,236
-[engine shuts off]
-[car door opens, shuts]

143
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:27,364
He's arrived at Yoshida Productions.

144
00:07:27,948 --> 00:07:29,240
The show is about to begin.

145
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:34,204
[footsteps approach]

146
00:07:39,626 --> 00:07:40,752
[door unlocks]

147
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:48,969
To the left as I come in.

148
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,640
The desk at the very back.

149
00:07:54,307 --> 00:07:55,767
The very bottom drawer.

150
00:08:12,892 --> 00:08:14,352
MANAGER
TAICHIRO YAMASHITA

151
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:18,665
[L] Now, Kira, how do you kill?
Show me!

152
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:23,795
We're in position
and ready to take him down.

153
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:25,922
-We'll move on your command.
-[L] Right.

154
00:08:27,465 --> 00:08:29,843
TAICHIRO YAMASHITA

155
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:32,095
[groans with pleasure]

156
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:38,685
He's not doing it. He just made
a note of his name before leaving.

157
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:40,854
So, he's not going to kill him here?

158
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:42,605
Ryuzaki, do you want us
to apprehend him?

159
00:08:42,939 --> 00:08:45,316
Negative. We still don't know
how he kills.

160
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:48,611
Perhaps he's planning to do something
once he's back in the car.

161
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:50,405
[L] Let's see camera one again.

162
00:08:52,282 --> 00:08:54,242
-[beeping]
-[clicking]

163
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:59,873
It's weird, you'd think he'd be desperate
to kill Matsuda this very second

164
00:08:59,998 --> 00:09:00,874
but he's calm.

165
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:02,500
It is strange.

166
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,002
If all he needed was the name,

167
00:09:04,085 --> 00:09:06,254
then he should have taken
the personnel file with him.

168
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:09,090
But he just put it back in its drawer
after taking the note.

169
00:09:09,174 --> 00:09:10,884
[Higuchi]
Thirty-six, 37...

170
00:09:11,426 --> 00:09:13,553
Thirty-eight, 39...

171
00:09:13,845 --> 00:09:15,180
Forty seconds.

172
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:20,018
[Matsuda] Kira is a cold-blooded murderer.
I can't forgive him for what he's done.

173
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:21,144
[grunts]

174
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:22,604
Damn, he didn't die.

175
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:25,982
[Light] What's he talking about?
He said he didn't die.

176
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:28,401
[L] Did he already try and kill Matsuda?

177
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:31,362
Was writing his name down
all he had to do, or was it...

178
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:32,864
What do we do know?

179
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:35,408
Should we just continue watching
what he's doing?

180
00:09:35,533 --> 00:09:38,411
What if he can cause a death
by just imagining it?

181
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:41,039
[L] I don't understand what's going on.

182
00:09:41,164 --> 00:09:43,541
I still can't figure out how
he kills people.

183
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:46,669
But even if we restrain him now
and try to get him to confess...

184
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:48,922
[MC] Only fifty minutes to go

185
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:50,507
-until the big Kira announcement!
-Damn!

186
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:51,591
I don't have any time!

187
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,968
-[phone dialing]
-[Light] He's making a phone call.

188
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:55,512
It's probably Misa again.

189
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:57,722
-[phone rings]
-[Misa] Yeah!

190
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:00,100
Huh?
[groans]

191
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,726
[yells]

192
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,020
[groans]

193
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:06,147
All right, calm down.

194
00:10:06,439 --> 00:10:07,816
I already know his face.

195
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:10,652
If I go back to company HQ
there should be surveillance videos

196
00:10:10,777 --> 00:10:11,861
from when he snuck in.

197
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,197
If I had the Shinigami eyes...

198
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:16,449
Half of my remaining lifespan, huh?

199
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,827
That's a lot. But if he makes
that announcement

200
00:10:18,952 --> 00:10:20,912
my life is as good as over anyway.

201
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:23,998
Better to have a life
that's short and sweet.

202
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:29,087
Rem, let's make the deal.

203
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:30,630
[high pitched ringing]

204
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:33,800
The deal? Who is this Rem person
he keeps talking to?

205
00:10:33,967 --> 00:10:37,887
Could it really be that Kira's power comes
from another world or some being?

206
00:10:38,012 --> 00:10:40,306
I really don't want to think
that's the case.

207
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,308
Then what is this Rem?

208
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:44,185
A Shinigami?

209
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,230
Whatever it is, we need
to keep watching him.

210
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:49,440
We'll learn nothing if we take him now.

211
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:52,485
We may still be able to find out
how he kills.

212
00:10:55,905 --> 00:10:58,533
[Higuchi] With these eyes
I'm invincible.

213
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:01,077
I have more than enough options now.

214
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:03,705
[engines rev]

215
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:05,999
[Soichiro Yagami] We're heading after him.

216
00:11:10,253 --> 00:11:11,254
[siren wails]

217
00:11:11,713 --> 00:11:14,757
[police] You in the red car,
pull over to the side of the road.

218
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:16,259
-[Higuchi grunts]
-[police] Now!

219
00:11:20,597 --> 00:11:21,472
[Wedy] This is bad.

220
00:11:21,556 --> 00:11:23,308
Higuchi's been pulled over by
a traffic cop.

221
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:27,020
[Wedy] I'm going to have to pass him
and leave the pursuit to Aiber's team.

222
00:11:27,145 --> 00:11:29,814
You were speeding. License, please.

223
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,441
Yeah, no problem.

224
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,943
Switch all screens to Higuchi's car.

225
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:37,447
[Higuchi] Let's see.
Where did I put it.

226
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:39,908
[high pitched ringing]

227
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,993
[Higuchi] This will take care of him.

228
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:43,536
YUKITO SHIRABA, ACCIDENT

229
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:45,205
[engine revs]

230
00:11:46,164 --> 00:11:47,290
[police] Hey!

231
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:49,626
Higuchi ditched the cop.
He's driving away.

232
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:51,252
[siren blares]

233
00:11:52,921 --> 00:11:54,422
What a bastard!

234
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:57,425
This is traffic control squad.
[cries out]

235
00:11:57,508 --> 00:11:58,885
[tires squeal]

236
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:05,642
That motorcycle cop just rear-ended
that truck. He's dead.

237
00:12:06,226 --> 00:12:08,019
He's dead?
By accident?

238
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:09,354
This is very bad.

239
00:12:10,188 --> 00:12:12,398
[L] All he did was put his hand
in his bag.

240
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:14,275
Could he have done something
in that moment?

241
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,818
More importantly,

242
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:19,113
how was he able to obtain
the name of the cop who stopped him?

243
00:12:19,614 --> 00:12:22,408
Does he only need a face,
like the second Kira?

244
00:12:23,618 --> 00:12:25,495
Rem. A deal.

245
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:29,165
[L] No, if he had the power to kill
by looking at someone's face,

246
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:31,417
he would have already killed
Matsuda by now.

247
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:34,921
What's going on?
Unless...

248
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:39,509
Everyone! It's too dangerous
to allow further action by Higuchi!

249
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:40,885
Let's bring him in.

250
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:43,930
[L] I believe he has the same powers
as the second Kira.

251
00:12:44,055 --> 00:12:46,557
He is able to kill
just by looking at someone's face.

252
00:12:46,683 --> 00:12:49,686
Please keep this in mind
when you move in to arrest him.

253
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:51,771
[cars approaching]

254
00:12:52,355 --> 00:12:54,315
[chuckles]

255
00:13:15,003 --> 00:13:17,797
[L] Watari, connect me
to the director of the NPA.

256
00:13:18,298 --> 00:13:19,173
[Watari]
Yes.

257
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:23,970
[L] This is L. We are now aware of
Kira's true identity.

258
00:13:24,262 --> 00:13:26,848
He's currently heading
from Hibiya to Shibuya

259
00:13:27,015 --> 00:13:30,101
along Highway Route One,
in a red sports car.

260
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:32,103
Our group will be handling the arrest.

261
00:13:32,186 --> 00:13:34,814
In the meantime,
please instruct all officers

262
00:13:34,897 --> 00:13:36,774
to refrain from approaching his car.

263
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:40,445
All right, Dad. During the next commercial
take measure seven.

264
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:41,779
Understood.

265
00:13:42,113 --> 00:13:44,115
Demegawa,
during the next commercial break,

266
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:46,200
swap Matsuda and the MC
with mannequins.

267
00:13:46,451 --> 00:13:48,995
We'll make it seem as if the broadcast
is continuing as normal

268
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:50,663
using the voices we've already prepared.

269
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:53,958
We'll leave the cameras running
and everyone evacuate the building.

270
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:57,420
So then, Light.
What say we go join the fun as well.

271
00:13:57,754 --> 00:13:58,671
Yeah.

272
00:13:59,464 --> 00:14:00,340
[Misa] Huh?

273
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:02,633
I'm sorry to do this, Misa,

274
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:05,303
but I have to make sure
you're restrained for a while.

275
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:07,847
[yelling] What? But that's...

276
00:14:08,181 --> 00:14:09,557
Stop joking around.

277
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:11,851
[helicopter propeller thrums]

278
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:19,567
[Light] I didn't realize you could pilot
a helicopter. That's incredible.

279
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:21,778
[L] Well, you can figure it out
with intuition.

280
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:27,116
[Light] Higuchi isn't going to Sakura TV.

281
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:28,493
He's headed the wrong way.

282
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:32,288
[L] Based on his route, I'd guess
he's coming to the Yotsuba main office.

283
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:34,665
[MC]
You've been outstandingly brave.

284
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:37,293
[Matsuda] No. I'm just doing
what anyone would do.

285
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,504
[Higuchi] If I go to the main office

286
00:14:39,629 --> 00:14:42,340
and find the surveillance video
with him on it, I can kill him.

287
00:14:42,632 --> 00:14:43,549
Come in, Wedy.

288
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:46,427
Have you removed absolutely everything
relating to Matsuda

289
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:47,887
at the Yotsuba headquarters?

290
00:14:48,096 --> 00:14:50,306
[Wedy] Yeah.
Why, is he headed there now?

291
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:52,058
Isn't that convenient.

292
00:14:52,308 --> 00:14:55,561
That should give me more than enough time
to go ahead and meet up with Mr. Yagami

293
00:14:55,645 --> 00:14:56,562
to set up the ambush.

294
00:14:59,315 --> 00:15:01,192
-[tires squeal]
-[car door opens, shuts]

295
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:03,319
[Higuchi] What the hell, I can't find him!

296
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:06,823
This is the right tape.
Someone must have erased it.

297
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:09,534
Did he come back
and erase them himself somehow?

298
00:15:09,659 --> 00:15:12,537
Or has someone from the group betrayed me
and started working with him?

299
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:16,290
No, doing that would not
absolve them of their crimes.

300
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:21,963
Who cares. I'm out of time.
I've got to hurry!

301
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:24,215
[engine starts]

302
00:15:24,298 --> 00:15:26,509
[MC] We're quickly approaching
the time for the announcement.

303
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:27,635
How are you feeling?

304
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:31,139
[Matsuda] I feel ready for this.
I really want you to do it now.

305
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:36,060
[MC] Yes, I understand. But let's cut to
a quick commercial break first.

306
00:15:36,227 --> 00:15:37,311
[Higuchi] Damn it!

307
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:40,189
I have to go to Sakura TV
and kill him there.

308
00:15:40,606 --> 00:15:41,607
[engine revs]

309
00:15:43,734 --> 00:15:47,488
Dad, Higuchi has left Yoshiba.
He's on his way to Sakura TV.

310
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:50,199
He'll be there in less than 15 minutes.
Are you ready?

311
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:53,244
[Yagami] I don't need my son asking
if I'm ready.

312
00:15:53,536 --> 00:15:54,787
Of course I am.

313
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:59,584
[MC] Is there anything more you'd like
to add before the announcement?

314
00:15:59,709 --> 00:16:03,129
[Matsuda] I want everyone to think hard
about Kira after he's caught.

315
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:04,714
People have to realize
that Kira is...

316
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:07,133
You ready, Mr. Yagami?
It's almost time

317
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:08,509
I know.

318
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:10,011
-[Wedy] Here.
-Hm?

319
00:16:10,261 --> 00:16:14,015
Aiber hates using guns.
Right now, I'm the only one armed.

320
00:16:14,599 --> 00:16:17,477
I can't take this.
I'm no longer a police officer.

321
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:19,979
Japanese law forbids civilians
from having guns.

322
00:16:20,146 --> 00:16:22,023
That means you shouldn't be
using one either.

323
00:16:22,773 --> 00:16:25,067
I guess you're as stubborn as always, huh?

324
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:26,652
SAKURA TV

325
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,072
[groans]
I made it in time.

326
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:37,205
Huh?

327
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:41,209
Why isn't anybody here?

328
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:45,505
Is it just in case the announcement
is true and Kira decides to retaliate?

329
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:49,175
Hm. At least it makes my job easier.

330
00:16:51,344 --> 00:16:54,430
[Mogi] We've arrived at Sakura TV.
We're moving into position.

331
00:16:55,473 --> 00:16:58,184
-Let's go, Aiber.
-Okay, Mogi!

332
00:16:58,559 --> 00:17:01,646
[MC] Right now we are being flooded
with phone calls and faxes

333
00:17:01,771 --> 00:17:03,481
showing support for
your courage and strength

334
00:17:03,898 --> 00:17:07,068
and demanding that Kira's identity
be revealed right away.

335
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:08,569
[Higuchi] Huh?

336
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,404
Even the studio is deserted.

337
00:17:11,989 --> 00:17:14,408
Still, I've got to be careful of
where the cameras are.

338
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:15,868
Can't let myself be seen.

339
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:18,287
[MC] ...beyond our control,
we will now end this broadcast,

340
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:19,372
[Higuchi] What?

341
00:17:20,164 --> 00:17:22,708
Dummies. This can't be!

342
00:17:22,917 --> 00:17:24,835
-[Yagami] Higuchi, hold it right there.
-[gasping]

343
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:26,254
[Wedy] Don't move!

344
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:33,386
I'd give up
if I were you.

345
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:36,764
You... you must be making
some kind of mistake.

346
00:17:36,973 --> 00:17:40,184
I'm only here to meet with Mr. Demegawa
and discuss something with him.

347
00:17:40,268 --> 00:17:41,644
[Higuchi] They're wearing tinted helmets.

348
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:43,938
They must be taking precautions
against Kira.

349
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,231
In that case...

350
00:17:45,690 --> 00:17:48,859
I'm with the Yotsuba Group,
from the Development Department.

351
00:17:48,985 --> 00:17:50,736
Let me show you my business card.

352
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:52,697
[Higuchi yells]

353
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:55,157
[grunting]

354
00:17:56,409 --> 00:17:57,493
[Aiber] No, Chief!

355
00:17:58,911 --> 00:17:59,912
[Wedy] Aiber!

356
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:04,458
Damn it!
I didn't want to use one of these, but...

357
00:18:08,671 --> 00:18:09,630
No!

358
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:13,009
L, Higuchi has a gun on him.
The chief has been shot.

359
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:14,594
Higuchi is escaping!

360
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,054
[Yagami] I'm all right. Sorry, Ryuzaki.

361
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:20,891
If we pursue him,
we can still catch him. Hurry!

362
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:23,561
This is bad. He's escaped from Sakura TV!

363
00:18:24,729 --> 00:18:25,813
[engine revs]

364
00:18:28,899 --> 00:18:30,109
[tires squeal]

365
00:18:32,903 --> 00:18:34,488
This leaves us no choice.

366
00:18:34,739 --> 00:18:36,907
We'll have to move in
and apprehend him.

367
00:18:37,325 --> 00:18:38,659
Watari, are you ready?

368
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:41,203
-Yes.
-[L] Light...

369
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:44,415
I think you should hold on to this
for self-defense.

370
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:46,167
This is Kira we're after.

371
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:49,462
No thanks.
Firearms aren't allowed in Japan.

372
00:18:50,046 --> 00:18:53,674
You know, I'm sure your father
would say the exact same thing.

373
00:19:01,766 --> 00:19:03,225
[honking]

374
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:06,062
He's driving like a maniac.

375
00:19:06,228 --> 00:19:08,064
-Don't lose sight of him.
-Yes.

376
00:19:12,068 --> 00:19:13,277
-[grunts]
-[tires squeal]

377
00:19:16,197 --> 00:19:17,615
[helicopter propeller thrums]

378
00:19:20,368 --> 00:19:21,994
[Higuchi]
What the hell was all that about?

379
00:19:22,078 --> 00:19:23,412
It had to be a trap.

380
00:19:23,788 --> 00:19:25,581
[TV announcer]
We now end our current broadcast

381
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:28,417
and return you to regular programming.
The evening news is next.

382
00:19:29,043 --> 00:19:32,546
[Higuchi] The program is over!
It didn't end just because I showed up.

383
00:19:33,047 --> 00:19:34,757
What the hell is going on?

384
00:19:35,925 --> 00:19:37,259
[cries out] What the...

385
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,974
[sirens wailing]

386
00:19:44,392 --> 00:19:46,268
Just like I thought, it was a trap.

387
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:48,270
Police cars with tinted windows?

388
00:19:48,396 --> 00:19:51,315
So all that stuff about
the police not going after Kira was a lie!

389
00:19:51,816 --> 00:19:52,983
They were preparing for this.

390
00:19:54,235 --> 00:19:55,319
[Watari]
What's happening?

391
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:58,572
I thought we told the police
not to get involved with the arrest.

392
00:19:58,823 --> 00:20:00,574
[Light] The only one
who would do this is...

393
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:02,410
Yes, you must be right.

394
00:20:11,377 --> 00:20:12,336
[grunts]

395
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:15,464
[tires squeal loudly]

396
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:17,800
[gasps]

397
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:28,686
Damn it! That way!

398
00:20:31,856 --> 00:20:33,190
Stop right there!

399
00:20:33,441 --> 00:20:34,692
[gasps]

400
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:53,127
[grunts]

401
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:55,546
Stay back!
Stay back or I'll shoot, I swear.

402
00:20:56,839 --> 00:20:57,757
[cries out]

403
00:21:08,601 --> 00:21:09,685
It's over.

404
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:12,938
Yes. It's over.

405
00:21:14,064 --> 00:21:17,067
[grunting]

406
00:21:26,577 --> 00:21:32,516
TO BE CONTINUED
